President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. Representative Barbara Lee and Representative Chris Smith will be nominated as Representatives of the United States to the Seventieth Session of the General Assembly of the United Nations. They will continue their duties in the United States House of Representatives while serving in this role. Representative Barbara Lee represents the 13th District of California and has served in various committees and leadership positions in Congress. Representative Chris Smith represents the 4th District of New Jersey and has also held various leadership positions in Congress, particularly in the area of foreign affairs. Cassandra Q. Butts, Senior Advisor to the CEO of the Millennium Challenge Corporation, will also be nominated as a Representative of the United States to the Seventieth Session of the General Assembly of the United Nations. She has a background in policy and legal work, including serving as Deputy White House Counsel and General Counsel to the Obama-Biden Transition Project.